# Deck slide reorder — safe workflow

**Tag this rule** (`@deck-slide-reorder`) when asking to move, renumber, or delete slides.

## Hard limits

- **Never** rewrite the deck HTML with Python, Node, or other bulk file scripts.
- **Never** delete a slide unless the user explicitly asks to delete it.
- **Never** `replace_all` on `/ 16` or `/ 17` — that breaks CSS like `aspect-ratio: 9 / 17`.
- **Only** edit `Pitch til Psykiatrifonden v2 (editorial).html`; then run `./sync-docs.sh` (do not hand-edit `docs/index.html`).

## How slides work

| What | Updates automatically? |
|------|------------------------|
| DOM order of `<section class="slide">` inside `<deck-stage>` | Manual (move blocks) |
| Left rail thumbnails | Yes — `deck-stage.js` on load |
| `data-screen-label`, `data-deck-slide` | Yes on load; set in HTML for consistency |
| `<span class="page-num">` (e.g. `03 / 16`) | **Manual** — must edit in HTML |
| HTML comments (`<!-- SLIDE N — … -->`) | Manual |

## Move one slide (two edits only)

1. **Insert** the full `<section>…</section>` block at the new position (update comment, `page-num`, `data-screen-label`, `data-deck-slide` in that block).
2. **Remove** the old copy using unique anchors (`data-om-id`, footer spans) — not a blind line range.

Do **not** cut-then-forget: insert first, then delete the duplicate.

## After every change — verify before syncing

```bash
# Must stay 16 unless user asked to add/remove a slide
grep -c 'section class="slide' "Pitch til Psykiatrifonden v2 (editorial).html"

# Each slide data-om-id on <section> must appear exactly once
```

Renumber shifted slides **high → low** (e.g. 13→12 before 12→11) to avoid double-replace collisions.

## Sync

```bash
./sync-docs.sh
```

User commits and pushes; agent must not push to live.
